ooked patties contaminated with fecal material containing the bacteria at a location in tacoma washington and other parts of the pacific northwest the chain was faced with several lawsuits each of which was quickly settled but left the chain nearly bankrupt and losing customers at the time washington state law required that hamburgers be cooked to an internal temperature of at least  °f  °c the temperature necessary to kill e coli bacteria although the fda requirement at that time was only  °f  °c which was the temperature jack in the box cooked after the incident jack in the box mandated that in all nationwide locations their hamburgers be cooked to at least  °f  °c additionally all meat products produced in the united states are required to comply with haccp hazard analysis and critical control points regulations every company that produces meat products is required to have a haccp plan that is followed continuously jack in the box also worked with food safety experts from manufacturing companies and created a comprehensive program to test for bacteria in every food product locationsedit second colorado location in arvada showing off the s logo new jack in the box in scottsdale arizona showing the new logo in  jack in the box announced plans for nationwide expansion by  as part of the initiative it is entering new markets as well as returning to markets where it had a presence in past years in support of this objective the chain began airing ads in states several hundred miles from the nearest location this is similar to a strategy used for years by sonic drivein in its national expansion efforts this jack in the box off us highway  is one of five company outlets in laredo texas notice the s logo the expansion strategy at that time was targeted at colorado delaware florida and texas in  the first new colorado store opened in golden marking an end to jack in the boxs yearlong absence from the state in albuquerque new mexico several locations opened in june  jack in the box restaurants last made an appearance in the albuquerque market approximately two decades ago in september  it was announced that  underperforming companyowned jack in the box restaurants located mostly in texas and the southeast would close in march  jack in the box launched the munchie mobile in san diego a food truck that will serve jacks burgers and fries in june  jack in the box launched their second food truck in the southeast region of the united statescitation needed another truck was launched for the northern texas area in april  in january  jack in the box opened its first of three locations in the indianapolis area a few months later the first ohio location opened in september  in west chester restatementedit on december   the company restated three years of results due to an accounting change that prompted the company to cut firstquarter and  earnings expectations see alsoedit list of hamburger restaurants companies portal food portal san diego portal referencesedit  jack in the box inc new  q quarterly report form q xbrl united states securities and exchange commission february     jack in the box inc new  annual report form k xbrl united states securities and exchange commission november     jack in the box inc aboutus retrieved    scotlandville su welcomes jack in the box franchise retrieved  dead link  lemons stephen february   bottom feeding phoenix new times retrieved    history jack in the box retrieved  february    langdon philip  orange roofs golden arches the architecture of american chain restaurants knopf p  isbn    furlonger jaye e july  the robert o peterson  russell forester residence pdf report california department of parks and recreation   jack in the box  youtube  retrieved    adams russell  americans eat  million jack in the box tacos a year and no one knows why the wall street journal p a subscription required help  alternate link via proquest  jack in the box debuts sirloin burger qsr magazine may     jack in the box adds ste