strategic plan centered on product innovation and multiple growth strategies to develop the regional chain into a national restaurant company in the last few years we have focused on building our brand enhancing food quality and promoting a core group of products while growing the chain primarily with companyoperated restaurants said chairman and ceo robert j nugent as a result since  we have increased our market share by  percent but todays environment presents new challenges and opportunities that require a fresh approach to satisfying consumer demands and expanding our companys size and value we expect this plan to build on our strengths and renew our momentum and help us grow more profitably over the longterm he explained following are highlights of the plan which was recently approved by the companys board of directors sales and profitability a focus on new product innovation to further differentiate the company from qsr competitors with a more relevant menu that includes lighter fare and additional quality enhancements to current product lines supporting this effort will be a new  sq ft innovation center scheduled to open in  that will house a rd kitchen quality assurance lab consumer research facility and marketing organization enhancement of the guest experience through continued speedofservice improvements and additional investments in interior design and exterior remodels multiple restaurant prototypes that reduce development costs improve unit economics and can be used in a greater variety of sites continuation of the profit improvement program to increase margins and returns targeted annual earnings per share growth of  percent multifaceted growth continuing its core growth strategy the company plans to increase the number of company restaurants by approximately  percent a year over the next five years about  percent will be the jack in the box cstores which cobrand a jack in the box restaurant with a convenience store and gas station this expanding concept offers several benefits such as additional sites additional sources of profits and cash flows and operating similarities with the core business continue to build new units in the southeast while strengthening the brand there and prepare the company for further newmarket expansion convert about  percent of existing company restaurants to franchises and add approximately  new franchise restaurants through the sale of development agreements the franchising plan will reduce the ratio of companytofranchised units from  today to approximately  in five years at this rate the company expects to be able to maximize the gains from franchise conversions actively evaluate for acquisition other restaurant concepts to supplement the companys core growth and balance the risk associated with growing solely in the highly competitive quickserve segment of the restaurant industry nugent commented that by strengthening the jack in the box brand and pursuing growth with more flexible options the company can better position itself as an increasingly profitable restaurant company many of the fundamentals of our business will remain but we believe that our new strategic plan will make us more competitive in a changing and more challenging environment as another element of its plan the company will continue to repurchase shares of jack in the box stock following recent approval by the board of directors of an additional  million for the companys stock repurchase program the program contingent upon bank authorization reflects managements confidence in the strategic plan and is intended to offset ongoing dilution from the exercise of vested stock options in addition to announcing its new strategic plan the company also provided its initial earnings guidance for fiscal  stating that it expects to earn on an asreported basis approximately  per diluted share versus  per share estimated in fiscal  the company expects to earn approximately  per diluted share versus  per share in fiscal  after adjusting fiscal  for the adoption of fas  in the first quarter of  conforming the companys income tax rate to the  estimated rate of  percent and excluding fourth quarter  estimated onetime charges for a litigation settlement and store closures other key figures provided systemwide sales of approximately  billion compared with an estimated  billion in fy  an increase of  percent samestore sales increase of approximately  percent compared with an estimated  percent decrease in fy  total revenues of approximately  billion  percent higher than the prior years estimated  billion gross profit rate of approximately  percent of revenue compared with  percent of revenue in fy  net earnings of approximately  million compared with approximately  million in the prior year excluding the onetime charges and adjusting for the adoption of fas  net earnings in the prior year would be approximately  million for a yeartoyear increase of  percent founded in  jack in the box is among the nations leading fastfood hamburger chains the company operates or franchises more than  quickserve restaurants in  states search form search subscribe tell us more… thank you for signing up to receive qsr’s flagship enewsletter am jolt to help us better serve the information needs of our audience please complete the information below first name last name company industry affiliation select from below franchisor franchisee independent consultant allied to industry job function select from below ceo  chief executive buyer  purchasing fb operations fb rd training  hr financial sales  marketing restaurant manager it  systems franchising  development brand development operations other in addition to am jolt we also offer the following enewsletters and communications please mark those you would like to receive whats on  a unique guide to the best in foodservice video from qsr and around the industry qsr promotions updates and information about happenings at qsr and its publisher journalistic inc qsr partner